==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Entreaty
<hw>En*treat"y</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Entreaties</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Treatment;
reception; entertainment.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>B.
Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act of entreating or beseeching; urgent prayer;
earnest petition; pressing solicitation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fair <qex>entreaty</qex>, and sweet blandishment.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Solicitation; request; suit; supplication;
importunity.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

